'''Maximiliano Javier Araújo Vilches''' (born 15 February 2000), known as '''Maxi Araújo''', is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|left-winger]] or [[left-back]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Sporting CP]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|541844}}</ref><ref name="auf">{{cite web|title=6 - Maximiliano Araújo|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/6-maximiliano-ara-uacute-jo/|accessdate=30 July 2019}}</ref>

==Club career==
Araújo is a youth academy graduate of [[Montevideo Wanderers F.C.|Montevideo Wanderers]]. He made his professional debut for the club on 11 March 2018 in a 2–1 league win against [[Montevideo City Torque]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://auf.org.uy/debutante-de-la-6a-fecha/|title=Debutante de la 6a fecha|date=16 March 2018|access-date=27 May 2024}}</ref>

At the end of December 2019 it was confirmed, Araújo had signed a deal until the end of 2023 with [[Liga MX]] club [[Club Puebla|Puebla]].<ref>[https://www.mediotiempo.com/futbol/liga-mx/uruguayo-maximiliano-araujo-reforzara-defensa-puebla El uruguayo Maximiliano Araujo reforzará la defensa de Puebla], mediotiempo.com, 27 December 2019</ref>

On 27 August 2024, Araújo joined [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Sporting CP]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.mx/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/14080254/maxi-araujo-nuevo-jugador-del-sporting-de-lisboa|title=Maxi Araújo, nuevo jugador del Sporting de Lisboa|language=es|date=27 August 2024|access-date=28 August 2024}}</ref> On 5 November 2024, Araújo scored his debut goal in the [[UEFA Champions League]] against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in a 4-1 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Sporting CP vs Man City: UEFA Champions League 2024/25 League phase |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2041974--sporting-cp-vs-man-city/ |access-date=2024-11-07 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
As a youth international, Araújo has represented Uruguay at the [[2019 South American U-20 Championship]], [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], [[Football at the 2019 Pan American Games – Men's tournament|2019 Pan American Games]] and the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/6-maximiliano-araujo/|title=6 - Maximiliano Araújo|date=16 January 2020|access-date=27 May 2024}}</ref>

On 21 October 2022, Araújo was named in Uruguay's 55-man preliminary squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Selección: Diego Alonso entregó la lista de 55 reservados para el Mundial de Catar|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Seleccion-Diego-Alonso-entrego-la-lista-de-55-reservados-para-el-Mundial-de-Catar-uc835965|date=21 October 2022|access-date=21 October 2022|language=es}}</ref> In June 2023, he received his first call-up to the [[Uruguay national football team|senior team]] for [[Exhibition game|friendly]] matches against [[Nicaragua national football team|Nicaragua]] and [[Cuba national football team|Cuba]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Siguen sumándose futbolistas convocados a los entrenamientos|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/siguen-sumandose-futbolistas-convocados-a-los-entrenamientos/|date=5 June 2023|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref> He made his debut on 14 June in a 4–1 win against Nicaragua.<ref>{{cite web|title=Selección: Bielsa eligió a Matías Viña como capitán en un equipo con muchos debutantes|url=https://www.futbol.com.uy/Deportes/Seleccion-Bielsa-eligio-a-Matias-Vina-como-capitan-en-un-equipo-con-muchos-debutantes-uc856920|date=14 June 2023|access-date=15 June 2023}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, Araújo was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Araújo is the elder brother of fellow professional footballer [[César Araújo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Maxi Araújo, y el sueño de compartir con su hermano César en la Celeste|url=https://www.espn.com.uy/futbol/mexico/nota/_/id/13330607/maximiliano-araujo-sueno-compartir-con-hermano-cesar-celeste-seleccion-uruguay|language=es|date=5 March 2024|access-date=28 August 2024}}</ref>

